title: "Jersey Shore's" Jenni 'JWoww' Farley Ties the Knot
text:
"Jersey Shore's" Jenni 'JWoww' Farley Ties the Knot Posted today at 12:00pm 
Peter Kramer/NBC (NEW YORK) -- Jersey Shore 's Jenni "JWoww" Farley and her fiance, Roger Mathews, tied the knot in New Jersey on Sunday. 
"This has been one of the greatest days in my life!" Farley, 29, tells Us Weekly . "I'm so happy to share this with our family and friends." 
JWoww's former Jersey Shore co-stars Nicole “Snooki” Polizzi, Deena Cortese, and Sammi “Sweetheart” Giancola were all bridesmaids. Her other co-stars Vinny Guadagnino, DJ Pauly D, and Ronnie Ortiz-Magro were also on hand. 
The couple’s 15-month-old daughter, Meilani, was the flower girl. 
"Big dress problems lol can't fit through the door," Farley captioned an Instagram photo of some dresses. 
We don't have any pictures of the reality star all dressed up for the big day, but on Friday she did share a picture of what she wore under her wedding dress. 
“For a woman about to get married on Sunday, she has been very calm,” Mathews wrote in a blog post on Farley’s official website on Friday. 
Mathews proposed to Farley in September of 2012, reportedly after the two went skydiving.
